ASABA – UNESCO Laureate, Prof Bashiru Aremu, has joined the Nigeria Labour Congress (NLC) and the nation’s workers to congratulate the pioneer president of the congress (1978-1984), Alhaji Hassan Adebayo Sunmonu, and his twin brother, Hussein Sumonu, on their 80th birthday on Thursday. Aremu, in a statement made available to newsmen in Asab, the Delta State capital, by his Special Adviser on Media and Publicity, Comrade Bieni Victor Emenike, the UNESCO Laureate, who rejoiced with the former NLC president and his twin brother, on the milestone, describing them as symbol of courage and national legacy. He described them as very courageous Nigerians, stating that the pioneer labour leader and his brother dedicated most of their working lives to public service since the early 1960s as workers with the then Ministry of Works and Surveys.